icies. He further said that the current tenure was too expensive as it required the state to hold elections every five years, thus having negative impact on the economy. Moonga reportedly said that these were his personal views not those of the ruling party. Moonga remarks came two months after President Edgar Lungu won the controversial August 11 election by just over 100 000 votes.&nbsp;Read more on this story here 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.